dfm1:ar

Digitally modelled analog filter [in :none, freq 1000, res 0.1, inputgain 1, type 0, noiselevel 3.0E-4] in - The input signal freq - The cutoff frequency of the filter res - The filter resonance (values > 1.0 may lead to self-oscillation) inputgain - Gain applied to the input signal which can be used to generate distortion type - Set to 0.0 for low-pass behaviour or 1.0 for high-pass noiselevel - The noisiness of the filter Provides low-pass and high-pass filtering. The filter can be overdriven and will self-oscillate at high resonances. Categories: Rates: [ :ar ] Default rate: :ar
